Adamowice [adamvits] is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Mszczonw, within yrardw County, Masovian Voivodeship, in east-central Poland. It lies approximately 6 kilometres (4 mi) south-west of Mszczonw, 13 km (8 mi) south of yrardw, and 48 km (30 mi) south-west of Warsaw.

